<span class="displaytext"><center><b> (candidate last): we won't ask un's permission to defend self-interest </b></center> <p><b> mclean, va </b> - senator (candidate full) issued the following statement today: </p><p>"during last night's debate in new hampshire, i was appalled that none of the leading (PARTY NAME) would stand up for israel's right to defend itself against iran--a country intent on acquiring nuclear weapons and whose leader has vowed to wipe israel off the map. a (candidate last) administration would stand by israel and all of our friends in the region. we would not wait for u.n. permission to support an ally or defend our interests abroad. the u.n. has not shown sufficient resolve toward stopping iran's nuclear ambitions."</p></span>



